.TH "LIBXTR-USERGUIDE" "3" "January 2026" "" "xtr"
.SH NAME
libxtr-userguide \- C++ logging library user guide
.SH OVERVIEW
.sp
The XTR API contains two classes; \fBxtr::logger\fP \%<#\:_CPPv4N3xtr6loggerE> and
\fBxtr::sink\fP \%<#\:_CPPv4N3xtr4sinkE>\&. Sinks each contain a queue [1], and
pass log messages to the associated logger via these queues. Each logger
has a background consumer thread which reads from the sinks that were created from the
logger. The background thread then formats the log message and either writes it
to disk or passes it to a custom back\-end if one is in use.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
+\-\-\-\-\-\-+
| Sink |\-\-\-[queue]\-\-\-+
+\-\-\-\-\-\-+             |
                     |     +\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-+
+\-\-\-\-\-\-+             +\-\-\-> |        |     +\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-+
| Sink |\-\-\-[queue]\-\-\-\-\-\-\-> | Logger |\-\-\-> | Back\-end; file/network/etc |
+\-\-\-\-\-\-+             +\-\-\-> |        |     +\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-+
                     |     +\-\-\-\-\-\-\-\-+
+\-\-\-\-\-\-+             |
| Sink |\-\-\-[queue]\-\-\-+
+\-\-\-\-\-\-+
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
An application is expected to use multiple sinks, for example a sink per thread, or
sink per component. To support this sinks have a name associated with them which
is included in the output log message. Sink names do not need to be unique and sink
log levels can be set individually.
.SH CREATING AND WRITING TO SINKS
.sp
Sinks are created by either:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
Calling \fBxtr::logger::get_sink()\fP \%<#\:_CPPv4N3xtr6logger8get_sinkENSt6stringE>\&.
.IP \(bu 2
Default construction followed by a call to \fBxtr::logger::register_sink()\fP \%<#\:_CPPv4N3xtr6logger13register_sinkER4sinkNSt6stringE>\&.
.IP \(bu 2
Copying another sink.
.UNINDENT
.sp
Copied sinks are registered to the same logger and have the same name as the
source sink. Sinks may be renamed by calling \fBxtr::sink::set_name()\fP \%<#\:_CPPv4N3xtr4sink8set_nameENSt6stringE>\&.
Once a sink has been created or registered, it may be written to using one of
several log macros which are described in the log macros \%<#\:log-macros>
section.
.SS Examples
.sp
Sink creation via \fBxtr::logger::get_sink()\fP \%<#\:_CPPv4N3xtr6logger8get_sinkENSt6stringE>:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
#include <xtr/logger.hpp>

xtr::logger log;

xtr::sink s = log.get_sink(\(dqMain\(dq);

XTR_LOG(s, \(dqHello world\(dq);
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
View this example on Compiler Explorer \%<https://\:godbolt\:.org/\:z/\:6MYYWzG4b>\&.
.sp
Sink creation via \fBxtr::logger::register_sink()\fP \%<#\:_CPPv4N3xtr6logger13register_sinkER4sinkNSt6stringE>:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
#include <xtr/logger.hpp>

xtr::logger log;
xtr::sink s;

log.register_sink(s, \(dqMain\(dq);

XTR_LOG(s, \(dqHello world\(dq);
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
View this example on Compiler Explorer \%<https://\:godbolt\:.org/\:z/\:qzqeMbGas>\&.
.sp
Sink creation via copying:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
#include <xtr/logger.hpp>

xtr::logger log;

xtr::sink s1 = log.get_sink(\(dqMain\(dq);
xtr::sink s2 = s1;

s2.set_name(\(dqCopy\(dq);

XTR_LOG(s1, \(dqHello world\(dq);
XTR_LOG(s2, \(dqHello world\(dq);
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
